  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Kailali Flood Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Christian Aid together with its local partner KPUS, will carry out its response in Joshipur and Kalari RMs  of Kailali district of Sudurpaschim Province  which is one of the most affected districts of the region by flood.  These two are most affected municipalities where ex-bounded labours are survivors of the crisis as they are most vulnerable in the municipalities due to social exclusion.  Targeted vulnerable HHs are from Christian Aid&#x2019;s regular programme geography and partner organization has been coordinating with RM and wards and community based on verification of affected vulnerable HHs data sheet developed by local authorities. Two RMs Joshipur and Kailari has requested our local partner KPUS to lead the response in municipality, where support from other development partners has not been observed till date. Remaining HHs of municipalities who will not get our direct support will be benefited from hygiene promotion and awareness at community level.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to reach out to 445 HHs through food assistance, support on temporary shelters, hygiene kit support and awareness raising on ways of hygiene promotion to avoid water borne diseases</narrative>
  </description>
